		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64392576"><p>In response to other comments here - it is not a contraction; it is not a possessive case; "it's not grammatically correct" is not correct but not necessarily wrong.</p><p>CEO's.</p><p>CEO is an acronym.<br>The title pluralizes the acronym (noun phrase Chief Executive Officer) which is used as a noun.<br>Plural of the acro-noun could be CEOs or CEO's.  There is no right or wrong, just a matter of convention.<br>Conventions about such usages of punctuation tend to evolve with time, even going back and forth.</p><p>In 1906, University of Chi<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64392576">

